<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted on behalf of English Heritage by Dave Batchelor, Head of Historic Environmental Intelligence (GSH0007)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:center; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">on behalf of English Heritage by Dave Batchelor, Head of Histo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ric Environmental Intelligence (GSH0007)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">English Heritage is Government’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">statutory adviser on the historic environment and an Executive Non-Departmental Public Body sponsored by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport, with its funding agreement signed by the Department for Communities and Local Government, and the Departme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nt for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs.  It was established by the National Heritage Act 1983 and seeks to broaden public access to England’s cultural heritage, increase people’s understanding and appreciation of the past, and conserve and enhance the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">historic environment.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In the past English Heritage picked up intelligence and undertook limited horizon scanning and foresight exercises. This happened in an ad-hoc way and there were no mechanisms for collating the intelligence or considering and acting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">upon the foresight or horizon scanning. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> More recently we have sought to recognise and integrate this work into our future work.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In 2011 English Heritage launched the National Heritage Protection Plan (NHPP) which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is a major strategy that identifies those</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> parts of England’s Heritage that matter to people most and are at greatest risk – and then concentrates efforts on saving them</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The plan recognises that t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">here are many public, commercial and voluntary organisations that ensure our heritage is cared for, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">appreciated and enjoyed.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">At the heart of the Plan is a clear set of priorities about what matters and what is in danger of being lost</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and where opportunities exist</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">These were identified following a widespread public consultation which is repeated every y</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ear to ensure the Plan remains up-to-date and relevant to changing circumstances.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The NHPP identifies eight measures, broad themes, which in turn are further subdivided into identifiable activities and cover all of our heritage protection activities these</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> measures are – </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">      </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 1 – Foresight</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 2 - Threat: Assessment and Response</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 3 - Understanding: Recognition/Identification of the Resource</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 4 - Understanding: Assessment of Character and Significance</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 5 -</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Responses: Protecting Significance</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 6 - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Managing Change</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 7 - Responses: Protecting and Managing Major Historic Estates</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Measure 8 - Responses: Help and Advice for Owners</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">As part of this, English Heritage has set out the contribution we inten</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d to make in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">all of the measures in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an Action Plan</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  This explains what we are doing to protect the heritage, why, where and when.  It makes our programme of work transparent and more accountable to the public than ever before.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The structure of the plan r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecognises the need for foresight to inform the subsequent actions within the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">measures and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">individual </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">activities.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In addition English Heritage established the Historic Environment Intelligence Team in 2011, they have been given a pivotal role in establishing the practice of horizon scanning and intelligence gathering within English Heritage and the wider sector. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In ad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dition they are looking </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">outwards </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">try to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ensure that the historic environment aspects are considered when other bodies are undertaking horizon scanning and foresight exercises. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In establishing the team and its working practices we have had to rely heav</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ily upon those that have already developed practices and methods which are proven. In particular we have drawn upon the published outputs from BIS and the DEFRA/NE/EA family. Within the wider Government framework we have found that there is little to draw </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">upon from the ‘cultural’ sector, with the exception of audience research or insight.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">One aspect of the teams work is to begin to move towards a more pro-active model of working. Currently English Heritage along with the majority of those in the sector, wh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ether in local government or the commercial sectors, operates within a highly reactive working environment. The need to prioritise and manage reducing resources, whist maintaining, or improving the protection for the historic environment, are very current </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reasons for adopting this approach.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How do Government departments make use of horizon scanning</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> - For reasons explained above English Heritage has very limited experience of interacting with Government departments or NDPBs. We therefore do not feel in the position to make any general statements about how the products of horizon scanning are being us</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed. That said those few times where we have engaged with other NDPBs in their horizon scanning exercises our contributions and views have been welcomed.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How effective is horizon scanning in Government? Do Ministers and senior officials consider horizon sc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">anning outputs appropriately?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> – For the same reasons as above we are not in a position to give answers to these questions. We have observed that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">there are often what may be termed behavioural reasons why horizon scanning is treated with degrees of sceptici</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sm, which from our position are unwarranted. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What changes could be made to improve existing horizon scanning activity?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">– From our limited experience we’ve noted the confusion that surrounds the different usages of the term horizon scanning, along with ot</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">her allied terms such as foresight. In paragraph 5 of his report Jon Day highlights this issue and goes onto to define horizon scanning for the purposes of the report. We would like to see this broadened out such that there were common terms and definition</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s used across Government and the NDPBs.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Will the recommendations made in Jon Day’s review of cross-government horizon scanning capability address current shortcomings?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">– Again from our limited experience it is likely that these recommendations will impro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ve the situation. The Day report recognises the need for both top down and bottom up approaches and we feel that the recommendations better cover the former and there is still work to be done to address the latter.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What progress has been made implementing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> these?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Not aware of any apart from the call for evidence.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">14</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How effective is the Government at responding to policy or regulatory challenges presented by new technologies?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">– One issue with new technologies is the apparent late engagement by Government and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">its NDPBs which means that these technologies are often developed without any reference to wider implications. Additionally this late engagement means that any necessary policy or regulatory matters are not considered alongside the development of the techn</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ology and therefore anything needed is often seen as an afterthought. Better horizon scanning should be able to pick up these developments and help avoid this scenario.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">15</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have one observation to make on the 3D printing case study. The ability of laser sc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">anners to capture artefacts and objects and then to send the data to a remote 3D printer opens up many opportunities across the historic environment sector. One such opportunity is the potential for museums to make available 3D images of artefacts which co</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uld then be printed out remotely, in effect a development of the collections on line approach which currently uses still or moving images. The ability for people to actually handle the object brings an added dimension which cannot be under estimated.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.english-heritage.org.uk/professional/protection/national-heritage-protection-plan/all-about-NHPP/</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">http://www.english-heritage.org.uk/professional/protection/national-heritage-protection-plan/plan/</span></p></body></html>